post.summary:
The POST method allows the client to send a set of companies that will be imported by the Mediusflow master data import queue.
The company will be created as a child company to either the root company or to another company provided

200.description: A link to the import batch, this link will give the status of how the batch is processing within XI

get.summary: The GET method will allow you to check status for an imported batch. When performing a POST, the link returned is pointed to this mehtod

parameters.name: importId
parameters.description: The import id is either retrieved byt he full link from the result of the POST or from within the XI master data import queue

delete.summary:
The DELETE mehtod will allow a client to remove an import item from the queue, this to allow an integration to take full responsibility
of resending master data batches and handle all error on the client side instead of Mediusflow. it's only possible to remove items that are not in a running state.

parameters.name: importId
parameters.description: The import id is either retrieved byt he full link from the result of the POST or from within the XI master data import queue
